.TH SHOREWALL-NFT-TCPRI 5 "2026-04-24" "shorewall-nft 1.10.2" "File Formats"
.SH NAME
shorewall\-nft\-tcpri \- PRIO qdisc band assignments for traffic shaping in shorewall-nft
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.I tcpri
file assigns traffic to bands in a PRIO qdisc (or similar priority-based
qdisc) based on protocol, port, address, or interface.  shorewall-nft
generates the corresponding
.BR tc (8)
commands via
.BR "shorewall\-nft generate\-tc" .
.PP
In addition to explicit band assignments, DSCP-marked traffic can be
mapped to priority bands: when a row specifies a DSCP value instead of
a port, the compiler emits an nft
.B meta priority set
.I dscp-value
.B vmap
rule so that DSCP\(->qdisc-priority translation happens in-kernel at
classification time without a separate
.BR tc (8)
filter.  The DSCP→band map is stored as a named nft verdict map in the
.I inet shorewall
table.

.SH FILE FORMAT
Location:
.I /etc/shorewall/tcpri
(or inside a merged
.IR /etc/shorewall46/ ).
.PP
Columns are whitespace-separated.  Lines beginning with
.B #
are comments.

.TS
l l l.
Column	Required	Description
_
BAND	yes	Priority band number (1=highest)
PROTO	no	Protocol filter
PORT	no	Destination port filter
ADDRESS	no	Destination address/CIDR filter
INTERFACE	no	Interface filter
HELPER	no	Conntrack helper match
.TE

.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Assign interactive traffic to the highest band:
.RS
.nf
#BAND  PROTO  PORT
1      tcp    22,23
1      udp    53
2      tcp    80,443
3
.fi
.RE

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR shorewall\-nft (8),
.BR shorewall\-nft\-tcdevices (5),
.BR shorewall\-nft\-tcclasses (5)

